  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Obese people pose specific problems as far as the management of airway during surgery. The
      study aims to compare efficacy and safety of two LMA devices.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The study will investigate two types of LMA devices endowed of different constructive
      features. The two devices share common features as far as providing access to the stomach and
      reducing morbidity of the upper airway. The two device differ in regard to ease of insertion
      and sealing of the airway and these features are particularly important in the obese patient.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
